Given that `hX : IsBernoulliOn X u p P`, which is defined as `HasLaw X Ber(u, p) P`, this means `map X P = Ber(u, p)`.

The key insight is that under the Bernoulli distribution `Ber(u, p)`, each element in `u` is independently included with probability `p`. So the marginal distributions for whether `i ‚ąą X` and whether `j ‚ąą X` should be the same when both `i, j ‚ąą u`.

I need to show that composing `X` with the function that checks membership of `i` gives the same distribution as composing with the check for `j`. This should follow from the symmetry of the Bernoulli distribution over elements in `u`.

The proof should use `map_map` to rewrite both sides in terms of `Ber(u, p)` and then show they give the same marginal distribution.

